The paper discusses a new class of algorithms for reinforcement learning, specifically for policy optimization problems in robotics. The paper also mentions the use of robust regression methods and the application of the algorithm to legged locomotion tasks. Based on this information, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision for the legged locomotion tasks, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of "gradient flows" and "off-policy updates" suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
